    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1868"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1868">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11H23/49.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>After continued insistence I have just procured from the Panama Government
                    payment of $5,000 in settlement of William T. Harrington claim. San Francisco, I
                    believe, is the home of his widow. I will send a draft to the Department by next
                    pouch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
